🎣 Phishing Awareness Analysis

DecodeLabs Cybersecurity Internship | Batch 2026 | Project 3

📌 Overview

Phishing Awareness Analysis is a Python-based cybersecurity project designed to identify phishing attempts in emails, SMS messages, and online communications. The program uses rule-based detection techniques to analyze suspicious content, calculate a risk score, classify the threat level, and recommend an appropriate security action.

This project demonstrates how cybersecurity concepts can be implemented using Python without relying on external libraries.

---

🎯 Objectives

- Detect phishing emails and messages.
- Identify suspicious URLs and keywords.
- Recognize common phishing techniques.
- Generate a risk score based on detected indicators.
- Classify messages as Safe, Suspicious, or Malicious.
- Recommend appropriate defensive actions.

---

🛠 Features

- Rule-based phishing detection.
- URL and sender analysis.
- Detection of urgency and social engineering tactics.
- Risk scoring system.
- Clear security recommendations.
- Interactive command-line interface.

---

🧠 Detection Techniques

The engine checks for several phishing indicators, including:

- Suspicious sender domains
- Fake login pages
- Dangerous attachments
- Password or OTP requests
- Urgent language
- QR-code phishing attempts
- Callback scams
- Deepfake or impersonation attempts
- Lookalike domains
- Sensitive information requests
- Social engineering tactics

---

⚙️ Risk Classification

Score| Classification| Action
0| 🟢 Safe| No Action Required
1–4| 🟡 Suspicious| Verify Before Responding
5+| 🔴 Malicious| Block and Report

---

💻 Technologies Used

- Python 3
- Regular Expressions (re)
- Standard Python Libraries

---

▶️ How to Run

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/Bhoomijaiswal28/Phishing-Awareness-Analysis.git

Move into the project folder:

cd Phishing-Awareness-Analysis

Run the program:

python phishing_triage_engine.py

